# CLAUDE.local.md — personal overrides (gitignored)

Copy this to `CLAUDE.local.md` for machine-local instructions that should NOT be
committed: `cp CLAUDE.local.md.example CLAUDE.local.md`

Claude Code loads `CLAUDE.local.md` in addition to the committed `CLAUDE.md`, and it
takes precedence for your personal preferences. It is gitignored, so it never reaches
the repo or your teammates.

Use it for things like:

```md
## My setup
- Production branch is `main`; Vercel auto-deploys from it.
- My local Supabase project ref: <ref>
- Skip the long preamble; I read code fast.

## Local-only reminders
- Rotate OPENROUTER_API_KEY before setting it in Vercel.
- Never run `vercel --prod` — I deploy via merge to main.
```

Keep it short. Anything the whole team needs belongs in the committed `CLAUDE.md`.
